Key Match Events: Adam Zampa took 3 wickets for 21 runs, becoming the tournament's leading wicket-taker.
Ben Stokes fell to Adam Zampa, letting out a howling 'no!' as he swept a catch to Marcus Stoinis.
Jos Buttler scored just one run before falling to Adam Zampa.
Moeen Ali's departure ended England's realistic hopes, and, after a brief flurry from David Willey (14), Chris Woakes (32) and Adil Rashid (20), Australia wrapped up the win with 33 runs to spare.
Post-Match Reflections: England's sixth defeat finally sees them mathematically out of contention to finish in the top four.
Mitch Marsh, having flown home to be with his family, will rejoin the squad in Mumbai by Monday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Mitchell Starc strangled Jonny Bairstow down the leg side off the very first ball.
Jonny Bairstow's wicket to the very first ball of the second innings gave Australia's chances a significant boost.
Travis Head's wicket in the sixth over left Australia at 38/2.

Cameron Green nearly gave away his wicket while also losing his bat, but England missed the chance despite four fielders converging in on the catch.
Others: Australia remain in contention of a semi-final spot with their fifth win in a row.
England's batters failed to back up the bowlers' fine work, sliding to yet another disappointing defeat.
